        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You arrange a spiky cage of bones, particularly tough vegetation, or other material to spring up when disturbed. The snare deals [[/r {9d8}[piercing]]]{9d8 piercing damage} to the first creature to enter this square; that creature must attempt a @Check[type:reflex|dc:31] save.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is knocked aside by the snare's deployment, taking half damage, and is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Flat-Footed]{Flat-Footed} until the end of its next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature is captured by the cage, taking full damage and falling @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Prone]{Prone}. It is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Immobilized]{Immobilized} while it remains within the cage. It can get free by @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Escape]{Escaping} (DC 31) or by destroying the cage (Hardness 5, HP 30, object immunities).</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but the creature takes double damage.</p>"
